title: Thompson, Leyva to regional
text:
Thompson, Leyva to regional Herald Democrat 
McKINNEY — Denison sophomore Aubyn Thompson and Sherman senior Oscar Leyva qualified for the Class 5A Region II cross-country meet with top 10 finishes at the District 10-5A race in McKinney on Monday. 
Thompson finished sixth in the girls race with a time of 20:26 while Leyva placed seventh on the boys side with a time of 17:26. 
Thompson was seven seconds from fifth place. Prosper’s Allie Taylor won the individual title in 19:44. 
Denison’s Katy Bonham was 34th in 22:51, Emory Redwine was 42nd in 23:34, Blakelee Stevens placed 50th in 25:05, Alisabeth Stanley was 52nd in 25:19 and Kinzy Cork was one spot back at 25:23. The Lady Jackets finished sixth overall. 
Prosper won the girls title, followed by McKinney North and Lovejoy. 
Sherman’s Ally Hampton was 39th with a time of 23:25 while Kelly Sibrian (23:25) and Genesis Zamora (23:28) immediately followed. Veronica Sosa was 44th with a time of 23:26, Diana Martinez was a place back in 23:40, Celeste Ramos was 49th in 24:33 and Leidy Sibrian was 51st in 25:07 as the Lady Bearcats finished eighth. 
Leyva was just a second from earning sixth place. Wylie’s Timothy Lee won the individual title in 16:33. 
Sherman’s Matthew Schulze was 13th in 17:46 while Jacob Charske was 20th in 18:06, Simon Scheibmeir was 24th in 18:18, Austin White took 29th in 18:27, Armando Arredondo was 33rd in 18:32 and Kevin Escobar was 45th in 19:15 as the Bearcats placed fourth. 
Denison’s Wilson Kirkbride was 34th in 18:34, Boston Byerly took 39th at 18:59, Devin Perez was a slot back in 19:01, Luke Altnether placed 47th in 19:32, Matthew Arbuckle finished 52nd at 19:48, Ben Carter was 54th in 22:29 and Liam Sartor was a spot behind in 23:05 as the Yellow Jackets placed eighth. 
The regional meet will be on October 26 in Arlington. Both Thompson and Leyva will attempt to be among the top 10 individuals not on the four teams qualifying for state to earn a spot at the UIL meet.
